I only pack a carry-on for my trips. ✈️ No waiting at the baggage claim, no risk of lost luggage – why would I ever go back to dragging around a suitcase?! 🧳 ⁠
⁠
It's easier than you think .😎⁠
⁠
How, you ask? 🤔 ⁠
⁠
💡1. First lay out several outfits, Clothing, shoes, handbags, accessories...you name it! And then asking: When and where am I wearing this ensemble?⁠
💡2. Shoes are a significant deal breaker as they can take over prized luggage real estate. I make sure that every pair is up to multiple outfits. Any pairs that are “one hit wonder”, instead of transferable to multiple outfits must be carefully considered before they earn their travel rewards.⁠
💡3. I'm a minimalist when it comes to beauty products. Instead of packing my entire vanity, I swap out hotel toiletries for shampoo and conditioner. My combo comb/brush is ready to create any look needed, and samples keep me smelling good long after check-out time - no need for a big bottle! Regarding makeup, there's room only in my bag for favorites and must-haves. I've also mastered space efficiency with one mini curling wand that does double duty as a flat iron.⁠
💡4. Who knew shoes could have a secret dual purpose? Transform yours into stylish mini-suitcases and pack 'em with your must-haves - like underwear, t-shirts, and brushes. Every inch counts! Let's get packing; in the shoe department, that is!⁠
💡5. Travel in style with my must-have plane accessory - a super versatile cardigan or jean jacket that works for any outfit, day and night!⁠
⁠
🎿 Skiing is the one thing standing between me and total travel freedom. I'm determined to find a way to fit skis, boots, AND all my adventure gear in a single carry-on. It's only a matter of time before my dream comes true. 🤩

🤔 Does anyone remember that scene in Austin Powers where he’s told not to say anything about the mole on the woman’s face that he is about the meet? ⁠
⁠
🙋🏻‍♀️And as soon as she walks in the room, all he can do is hyper-fixate on it. And the first word to come out of his mouth is mole? Moley, Moley, moley!! 😮 ⁠
⁠
🥨Well, that’s how I feel when somebody tells me not to eat something. Tell me not to eat carbs and forget it. The next thing you know, I have pasta for breakfast, lunch, and dinner. 🥐🥨🥖🍞🥯⁠
So I’ve come to understand that deprivation does not work for me. What does work is adding more of the good stuff when my pants are feeling a little snug. More veggies, more lean proteins, more water, and more walking. ⁠
⁠
Does anyone else feel this way? #moley ⬇️⁠

🚶‍♀️🧠🧘‍♀️ Today is National Walking Day, a day to celebrate the many benefits of walking for our mind, body, and spirit.⁠
⁠
Walking is a simple and accessible exercise with numerous physical and mental health benefits. 💪 It can help improve cardiovascular health, strengthen muscles and bones, and even reduce the risk of chronic diseases such as diabetes and heart disease. But the benefits of walking go beyond physical health.⁠
⁠
Walking is also great for mental health, helping to reduce stress, anxiety, and depression and improving mood and overall well-being. 🧘‍♀️ Taking regular walks in nature can be especially beneficial, as it can boost creativity, attention, and cognitive function.⁠
⁠
In addition to these physical and mental benefits, walking can also be a spiritual experience. 🙏 Whether it's walking a labyrinth, meditation, or taking a meditative stroll through nature, walking can help us connect with ourselves, our environment, and our higher power.⁠
⁠
So, on this National Walking Day, let's celebrate and embrace the many benefits of walking for our mind, body, and spirit. Whether taking a stroll, picking up the pace with a brisk walk, or practicing a walking meditation, let's make walking a regular part of our daily routine. 💪🧠🌳⁠
